oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tennessee Central Railroad
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph which shows a section of the Tennessee Central Railroad near a tunnel in Rockwood, Tennessee. Two women and a man are posing for the photo with a barrel in front of them. Several railroad workers can be seen in the background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
